1234567890 xozszn HOZD 1/3 @ 1a ;#& ? % $ ! In August of 2016, four unlikely collaborators in the world of type, fonts and font technology stood on a stage at the ATypI conference in Warsaw, Poland. The collaborators were Apple, Microsoft, Adobe and Google. Together they announced the publishing of OpenType 1.8, an update to the now ubiquitous font standard which was originally an amalgam of Apple & Microsofts TrueType, and Adobes PostScript font formats. The OpenType 1.8 announcement, ATypI, Warsaw, Poland, September 14, 2016.
